	dprr:hasNoteText "Tr. pl. 449. The manuscript tradition of Livy 3.54.13 favors the praenomen Ap. rather than the P. adopted by Sigonius and the Conway-Walters text. See Ogilvie, Comm. Liv. 496-497.\n" .
